  "body": "<!-- \r\nBy filing an Issue, you are expected to comply with the Code of Conduct, \r\nincluding treating everyone with respect:\r\nhttps://github.com/Consensys/teku/blob/master/CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md\r\n\r\nNot all sections will apply to all issue types.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n### Description\r\ncurrently using Web3signer with TLS + http basic auth. This work fine with Lighthouse and Prysm when using an URL format of https://user:pass@web3signer_url but in TEKU it seems that the HTTP lib used does not support passing the basic auth credentials. \r\n\r\n```\r\n2023-12-07 09:10:36.137 ERROR - External signer is currently not reachable at https://w3s:PASSWORD@web3signer.sepolia.domain.com\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen logged into the pod I can query it fine.\r\n\r\nIs there any way to support this easily in TEKU ? Or am I missing something ? Right now I'm passing this as en ENV var, I could try via config or args but not sure it would change anything.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\nSet the env vars TEKU_VALIDATORS_EXTERNAL_SIGNER_URL.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\n\r\nConnection is successful\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** \r\n\r\nUnable to connect\r\n\r\n**Frequency:** \r\n\r\nConstant\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: 23.08\r\n* Java version: jdk17\r\n* OS Name & Version: Ubuntu 22.04 but running in Kubernetes via Docker image\r\n* Docker Version: No docker but containerd\r\n* Cloud VM, type, size: Bare metal\r\n",
